{"nameWithOwner":"ls-age/babel-preset","url":"https://github.com/ls-age/babel-preset","description":"Babel preset used by ls-age","pushedAt":"2019-04-12T11:34:24Z","stargazers":{"totalCount":0},"releases":{"nodes":[{"tagName":"v0.4.0"}]},"readme":{"title":"@ls-age/babel-preset","slug":"ls-agebabel-preset","sections":[{"title":"Install","slug":"install"},{"title":"Usage","slug":"usage","children":[{"title":"Via .babelrc / &quot;babel&quot; field in package.json (Recommended)","slug":"via-babelrc-andquotbabelandquot-field-in-packagejson-recommended"},{"title":"Via CLI","slug":"via-cli"},{"title":"Via Node API","slug":"via-node-api"}]},{"title":"Options","slug":"options","children":[{"title":"target","slug":"target"}]}],"content":"<h1 id=\"ls-agebabel-preset\">@ls-age/babel-preset</h1><blockquote>\n<p>Babel preset used by ls-age</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"install\">Install</h2><pre><code class=\"language-sh\">npm install --save-dev @ls-age/babel-preset</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage</h2><h3 id=\"via-babelrc-andquotbabelandquot-field-in-packagejson-recommended\">Via <code>.babelrc</code> / &quot;babel&quot; field in <code>package.json</code> (Recommended)</h3><pre><code class=\"language-json\">{\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">\"presets\"</span>: [<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"@ls-age/babel-preset\"</span>]\n}</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"via-cli\">Via CLI</h3><pre><code class=\"language-sh\">babel script.js --presets @ls-age/babel-preset</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"via-node-api\">Via Node API</h3><pre><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">require</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"@babel/core\"</span>).transform(<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"code\"</span>, {\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">presets</span>: [<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"@ls-age/babel-preset\"</span>]\n});</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"options\">Options</h2><p>Options passed to the prefix can be a string or an object. When a string is given it is assumed to be the <code>target</code> option. Therefore</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-json\">{\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">\"presets\"</span>: [\n    [<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"@ls-age/babel-preset\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"browser\"</span>]\n  ]\n}</code></pre>\n<p>equals</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-json\">{\n  <span class=\"hljs-attr\">\"presets\"</span>: [\n    [<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"@ls-age/babel-preset\"</span>, { <span class=\"hljs-attr\">\"target\"</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"browser\"</span> }]\n  ]\n}</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"target\"><code>target</code></h3><p><code>&quot;node&quot; | &quot;browser&quot;</code>, defaults to <code>&quot;node&quot;</code></p>\n<p><strong>All other options are passed directly to <a href=\"https://github.com/babel/babel/tree/master/packages/babel-preset-env\">babel-preset-env</a></strong></p>\n"}}